## Key Themes Emerging from Research

Based on content collected so far, five high-signal themes are emerging across experts:

1. **Founder-led content beats company pages** — Personal profiles consistently outperform brand accounts algorithmically and in trust-building (Gerhardt, Moubeche, Walker)

2. **Systems over inspiration** — The experts generating real pipeline treat LinkedIn as a production system, not a creative exercise (Welsh, Acosta, Reed)

3. **Positioning before content** — Without clear ICP positioning, even well-written LinkedIn posts fail to convert (Dunford, Bourgoin, Natividad)

4. **Dark social attribution gap** — Most LinkedIn-driven pipeline is invisible to CRM attribution — measurement must shift to self-reported data (Walker, Natividad)

5. **Zero-click content as the new standard** — Posts that deliver full value in-feed outperform posts that drive to external links, both algorithmically and in trust-building (Natividad, Welsh, Simmonds)

